race.comment: BRAZEN DIVA (10) settled midfield then made some ground but was never a threat last start over 1009m at Yarra Valley. Stepping up to 1100m for the first time this prep is key her fortunes - she has raced twice at this trip for two placings. Rock hard fit and ready to win. FARNANHEIT (8) for the Freedman camp is back from a seven-month spell. Best of two runs in the maiden campaign was the last effort when beaten only half a length over 1200m at Ballarat Synthetic. A strong recent jump-out at Cranbourne will have him ready to run well.  PULL MY FINGER (5) missed the placings for the first time in his four-start career at Yarra Valley a month ago. Freshened up and will enjoy this slightly longer journey. SOMETHINGINTHEAIR (7) ran out of condition late when resuming over 1000m at Cranbourne recently. Fitter and should be far more competitive. FULHAMZEDGE (1) has been easily accounted for at both runs to date but might improve with the application of blinkers.
